        "pred_labels": "modify-skill-metadata, add-example, add-review-round, add-reference-doc, add-voice-rule, tighten-instruction-wording",
        "messages": "## Commit messages\n\n\n```\nfeat: improve 27 curated skill definitions via tessl skill review\n\nHullo @ComposioHQ 👋\n\nI ran your skills through `tessl skill review` at work and found some targeted improvements. Here's the before/after for the top 10 most improved:\n\n| Skill | Before | After | Change |\n|-------|--------|-------|--------|\n| content-research-writer | 26% | 96% | +70% |\n| file-organizer | 30% | 96% | +66% |\n| competitive-ads-extractor | 26% | 89% | +63% |\n| skill-share | 26% | 89% | +63% |\n| image-enhancer | 36% | 96% | +60% |\n| domain-name-brainstormer | 34% | 89% | +55% |\n| changelog-generator | 43% | 96% | +53% |\n| lead-research-assistant | 41% | 93% | +52% |\n| tailored-resume-generator | 38% | 89% | +51% |\n| brand-guidelines | 56% | 100% | +44% |\n\nAll 27 curated skills were reviewed and optimized. Average score went from 56% to 93% (+37%).\n\n<details>\n<summary>Changes made across skills</summary>\n\n- **Expanded frontmatter descriptions** with explicit \"Use when...\" trigger clauses and comprehensive natural-language trigger terms\n- **Removed verbose explanations** of concepts Claude already understands (filler words, obvious definitions, marketing copy)\n- **Added executable code examples** — concrete commands, Python snippets, regex patterns replacing vague procedural descriptions\n- **Added validation checkpoints** and error handling to workflows\n- **Improved progressive disclosure** — referenced external files where appropriate instead of inlining everything\n- **Consolidated redundant sections** — replaced repetitive prose with compact reference tables\n- **Switched to third-person voice** in descriptions (per skill authoring best practices)\n- **Net reduction of ~2,265 lines** across 27 files while increasing actionability\n\n</details>\n\nHonest disclosure — I work at @tesslio where we build tooling around skills like these. Not a pitch - just saw room for improvement and wanted to contribute.\n\nIf you want to run reviews, evals and optimizations yourself, just `npm install @tessl/cli` then run `tessl skill review path/to/your/SKILL.md`, and click [here](https://tessl.io/registry/skills/submit) to find out more.\n\nThanks in advance 🙏\n```",
