        "pred_labels": "script-fix-logic-bug, script-fix-platform-compat",
        "messages": "## Commit messages\n\n\n```\nfix(clv2): support CLV2_CONFIG override in start-observer.sh\n\nobserve.sh already supports the CLV2_CONFIG environment variable to\noverride the config.json path, but start-observer.sh hardcodes\nSKILL_ROOT/config.json. When ECC is installed as a plugin, SKILL_ROOT\nresolves to the plugin directory instead of ~/.claude/skills/, so the\nuser's config (with observer.enabled: true) is never read.\n\nThis is particularly impactful on macOS where the observer lazy-start\nrequires lockfile (procmail) — without the correct config path, the\nobserver never starts even when properly configured.\n\nApply the same CLV2_CONFIG override pattern from observe.sh to\nstart-observer.sh for consistency.\n```\n\n```\nfix(clv2): fix observer sandbox issues on macOS\n\nTwo issues prevented the observer Haiku agent from working:\n\n1. Temp files created in TMPDIR (/var/folders/ on macOS) are\n   inaccessible to the sandboxed Claude agent spawned by observer-loop.\n   Move analysis and prompt files to PROJECT_DIR instead.\n\n2. Claude CLI does not have a --cwd flag. Use --add-dir to grant\n   the sandboxed agent read/write access to the project directory\n   where instinct files live.\n\nTested: observer now successfully reads observations and can write\ninstinct files on macOS.\n```",
        "pred": "## What axis\n\n\n**pred_labels:** `script-fix-logic-bug`, `script-fix-platform-compat`\n\n**families:** `script`\n\n**what_expression:** `summarize-skill-object-change`, `illustrate-skill-function`, `describe-skill-implementation-principle`\n\n\n## Why axis\n\n\n**why_expression:** `describe-skill-issue`, `describe-skill-objective`\n\n**why_intentions:**\n\n- support CLV2_CONFIG override in start-observer.sh so user config is read when installed as plugin\n\n- fix observer sandbox issues on macOS\n\n\n## Evidence\n\nstart-observer.sh hardcodes config.json so user config is never read; fix observer sandbox issues on macOS (TMPDIR inaccessible, no --cwd flag)",
