        "pred_labels": "script-fix-logic-bug",
        "messages": "## Commit messages\n\n\n```\nfix(skill-creator): eval-viewer HTML breakout + metadata search depth\n\nTwo bugs in generate_review.py:\n\n1. User-generated outputs containing `</script>` (e.g. code samples\n   showing gtag.js integration) break out of the embedded `<script>`\n   block, corrupting the entire viewer HTML. Fix: escape `</` to `<\\/`\n   after `json.dumps()` — both forms are valid JSON (RFC 8259 §7) and\n   the browser's HTML parser no longer sees a premature script\n   terminator.\n\n2. `eval_metadata.json` is only searched 1 level up from `run_dir`,\n   but the canonical workspace layout places it 2 levels up\n   (`eval-N/eval_metadata.json` vs `eval-N/with_skill/run-1/`).\n   This causes all prompts to show as \"(No prompt found)\" in the\n   viewer. Fix: add `run_dir.parent.parent` to the search path.\n```",
        "pred": "## What axis\n\n\n**pred_labels:** `script-fix-logic-bug`\n\n**families:** `script`\n\n**what_expression:** `summarize-skill-object-change`, `illustrate-skill-function`, `describe-skill-implementation-principle`\n\n\n## Why axis\n\n\n**why_expression:** `describe-skill-issue`, `describe-skill-objective`\n\n**why_intentions:**\n\n- fix HTML breakout from embedded script block when outputs contain </script>\n\n- fix eval_metadata.json search depth so prompts are found\n\n\n## Evidence\n\nTwo bugs in generate_review.py; outputs containing </script> break out of the embedded script block; escape </ to <\\/; eval_metadata.json only searched 1 level up but layout places it 2 levels up; add run_dir.parent.parent",
