        "messages": "## Commit messages\n\n\n```\nfeat(brainstorming): add context reset option after design doc\n\nAfter brainstorming completes and the design doc is committed to file,\nthe accumulated context (Q&A, exploration, approach comparisons) is\nalready captured in the document. Offer users the choice to start a\nfresh session for writing-plans, freeing up context window space.\n```\n\n```\nUpdate skills/brainstorming/SKILL.md\n```\n\n```\nfix(brainstorming): fix terminal-state docs and add worktree step to handoff\n\n- Mark both terminal nodes as doublecircle in the process flow graph\n- Update prose to describe both terminal states (fresh session vs continue)\n- Add using-git-worktrees step to fresh-session and continue handoff paths,\n  matching writing-plans skill's worktree requirement\n```\n\n```\nUpdate skills/brainstorming/SKILL.md\n```\n\n```\nfix(brainstorming): narrow skill ban to implementation skills only and add worktree step\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n```\n\n```\ndocs(writing-plans): document design doc input mechanism from brainstorming\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n```\n\n```\nrm hud-state.json\n```\n\n```\nrm hud-stdin-cache.json\n```\n\n```\nfeat: add dynamic model selection skill for cost-optimized subagent dispatch\n\nIntroduces a new skill that guides agents to select the appropriate model\ntier (opus/sonnet/haiku) based on task complexity, reducing costs by\navoiding opus for tasks where sonnet or haiku suffice.\n\n- New skill: dynamic-model-selection with routing table and decision flowchart\n- Updated dispatching-parallel-agents with model selection step\n- Updated subagent-driven-development with per-role model recommendations\n- Updated implementer/reviewer prompt templates with recommended models\n- Changed code-reviewer agent default from inherit to sonnet\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_011VwmZeBABhQDre7J313fB8\n```\n\n```\nfeat: rebalance agent model allocation for better opus utilization\n\nCode quality reviewer now defaults to opus (was sonnet) since quality\nreview genuinely benefits from deeper reasoning about coupling, edge\ncases, and architectural drift. Implementer escalation criteria broadened\nto include multi-file changes and new subsystem creation. Spec reviewer\ngains escalation path for complex multi-requirement specs.\n\nChanges ratio from 15 sonnet + 1 opus to 10 sonnet + 6 opus per\n5-task session (~40% cost reduction vs all-opus while maintaining\nhigh quality gates).\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_011VwmZeBABhQDre7J313fB8\n```\n\n```\nfeat: fork superpowers for Claude Code exclusive use\n\nStrip all non-Claude Code platform support from obra/superpowers v4.3.1.\n\nRemoved: .codex/, .opencode/, .cursor-plugin/, lib/skills-core.js,\ntests/opencode/, platform-specific docs, Cursor compat in session-start hook.\nREADME clarifies fork origin. RELEASE-NOTES reset to v5.0.0.\n```\n\n```\ndocs: update all project paths to KyongSik-Yoon/superpowers-claude\n\n- plugin.json: update homepage, repository, author\n- marketplace.json: update owner and plugin author\n- README.md already updated in previous commit\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01JHgaqnf5Fw7CQMS38dd6V7\n```\n\n```\ndocs: simplify installation to single command\n```\n\n```\nfeat: add [model] prefix convention to agent descriptions\n\nInclude model name (opus/sonnet/haiku) in agent description so the\nagent list shows which model each uses without expanding.\n```\n\n```\nfeat: add context reset recommendation to writing-plans handoff\n\nBrainstorming + plan writing consumes significant context window.\nRecommend fresh session before implementation so full context is\navailable for the implementation phase.\n```\n\n```\nrefactor: remove context reset from brainstorming, defer to writing-plans\n\nBrainstorming context (Q&A, decisions, rejected approaches) is valuable\nfor writing a good plan. Context reset now happens only after\nwriting-plans completes, right before implementation.\n```\n\n```\nrefactor: simplify execution handoff to /clear with plan path\n\nInstead of asking user preference, just give a ready-to-use command\nblock with /clear and the plan file path. User copies and runs it.\n```\n\n```\nfix: use English for execution handoff message\n```\n\n```\nfeat: use AskUserQuestion for execution handoff selection\n\nPresent clickable UI options instead of text block. User can select\n/clear + execution skill or continue in session with one click.\n```",
