        "messages": "## Commit messages\n\n\n```\nchore: ignore macOS finder metadata files\n```\n\n```\nfeat: migrate batch2 code review skills for codex workspace\n```\n\n```\nfeat: migrate batch4 completion and skill-authoring workflows\n```\n\n```\nfeat: migrate batch3 parallel and subagent workflows\n```\n\n```\ndocs: align codex wording in migrated skills\n```\n\n```\ndocs: clarify skill access fallback\n```\n\n```\ndocs: align skill access wording with implicit selection\n```\n\n```\nchore: normalize migrated runtime skills and worktree defaults\n```\n\n```\ndocs: update default worktree directory preference in skill documentation\n```\n\n```\ndocs: require requesting-code-review in execution workflows\n```\n\n```\ndocs: gate writing-plans handoff by delegation capability\n```\n\n```\ndocs: clarify implementation setup instructions in brainstorming skill\n```\n\n```\ndocs: enhance reviewer prompt and add comprehensive review checklist for code quality and production readiness\n```\n\n```\nSet local code-review default in skills and journal\n```\n\n```\ndocs: add prompt for implementer to use superpowers-receiving-code-review skill\n```\n\n```\ndocs(skills): add guidance for using separate branch and worktree in executing plans skill\n```\n\n```\nFix reviewer prompt markdown fence rendering\n```\n\n```\nfix: restore polyglot wrapper to fix Windows hook window spawning\n\nClaude Code spawns hook commands with shell:true + windowsHide:true,\nbut on Windows the execution chain cmd.exe -> bash.exe causes Git\nBash (MSYS2) to allocate its own console window, bypassing the hide\nflag. This creates visible terminal windows that steal focus on every\nSessionStart event (startup, resume, clear, compact).\n\nThe fix:\n- Rename session-start.sh to session-start (no extension) so Claude\n  Code's .sh auto-detection regex doesn't fire and prepend \"bash\"\n- Restore run-hook.cmd polyglot wrapper to control bash invocation\n  on Windows (tries known Git Bash paths, then PATH, then exits\n  silently if no bash found)\n- On Unix, the polyglot's shell portion runs the script directly\n\nThis avoids Claude Code's broken .sh auto-prepend, gives us control\nover how bash is invoked on Windows, and gracefully handles missing\nbash instead of erroring.\n\nAddresses: #440, #414, #354, #417, #293\nUpstream: anthropics/claude-code#14828\n```\n\n```\nupdate 'Verify Installation' section\n\n'Verify Installation' section with updated instructions.\n```\n\n```\nfix: quote CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT for spaces, use POSIX-safe path resolution\n\n- Quote ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT} in hooks.json to handle paths with spaces\n  (e.g. \"C:\\Users\\Robert Zimmermann\\...\")\n- Replace bash-only ${BASH_SOURCE[0]:-$0} with POSIX-safe $0 in\n  run-hook.cmd so the Unix path doesn't break on dash (/bin/sh)\n\nAddresses: #518 (spaces in path), Ubuntu/Debian compatibility\n```\n\n```\ndocs(plans): add handoff prompt format design\n```\n\n```\ndocs(plans): add handoff prompt format implementation plan\n```\n\n```\ndocs(journal): record handoff prompt format decision\n```\n\n```\ndocs(skills): remove reviewer prompt heading from handoff template\n```\n\n```\ndocs(skills): require single fenced reviewer handoff block\n```\n\n```\ndocs(skills): add parallel-session implementer handoff template\n```\n\n```\ndocs(skills): define parallel handoff prompt output contract\n```\n\n```\ndocs(skills): align handoff placeholders across review and plan prompts\n```\n\n```\ndocs(skills): update skill references to use variable syntax in reviewer and implementer prompts\n```\n\n```\ndocs(skills): update implementer prompt to use variable syntax for skill reference\n```",
        "pred": "## What axis\n\n\n**pred_labels:** `retarget-host-tooling`, `script-fix-platform-compat`, `rename-or-reorganize-structure`, `add-review-round`, `add-procedure-step`, `add-output-format-spec`, `add-prompt-template-resource`, `tighten-instruction-wording`, `fix-skill-instruction-bug`, `change-artifact-storage`, `add-decision-rule`, `style-or-format-content`, `remove-auxiliary-file`, `add-reference-doc`\n\n**families:** `decision`, `fix`, `lifecycle`, `polish`, `procedure`, `resource`, `retarget`, `script`, `spec`\n\n**what_expression:** `summarize-skill-object-change`, `illustrate-skill-function`, `describe-skill-implementation-principle`\n\n\n## Why axis\n\n\n**why_expression:** `describe-skill-issue`, `describe-skill-objective`, `illustrate-skill-requirement`\n\n**why_intentions:**\n\n- migrate skills to Codex-native workspace\n\n- fix Windows hook window spawning via polyglot wrapper\n\n- quote plugin root path for spaces and POSIX-safe path resolution\n\n- define handoff prompt output contract and align placeholders\n\n- set local code-review default",
