        "messages": "## Commit messages\n\n\n```\nchore(config): update homepage and repository URLs\n\nCorrects the project's homepage and repository links to point to the active GitHub user account, ensuring accurate resource references.\n```\n\n```\ndocs(install): update superpowers repo URL\n\nCorrects the repository URL for cloning the superpowers skills in the installation guide.\n\nEnsures users clone from the updated and maintained source.\n```\n\n```\nrefactor(skills): clarify skill usage and opt-out rules\n\nUpdates skill descriptions to emphasize explicit user requests for activation.\n\nAdds a process gating step to skip discipline skills when users opt out, except for high-risk cases.\n\nProvides detailed opt-out signals, risk overrides, rationalizations, and priority guidance to improve context-sensitive skill invocation.\n\nEnhances clarity and flexibility in skill handling to better respect user preferences while maintaining safety.\n```\n\n```\nfeat(skills): add opencode, testing, and logging skills\n\n- opencode: reference skill for OpenCode CLI (commands, config, gotchas)\n- testing: pattern skill for test strategy (applies when no project guidelines)\n- logging: pattern skill for structured logging (applies when no project guidelines)\n\nEach skill has stable SKILL.md and separate evolving content files.\n```\n\n```\ndocs(skills): clarify logging and testing descriptions\n\nUpdates skill descriptions to include reviewing and improving activities for logging and testing.\n\nEnhances guidance clarity when explicit project guidelines are absent.\n```\n\n```\ndocs(logging): add guidelines for console logging\n\nAdds best practices for using console methods with context objects\nEncourages structured logging over string concatenation for better clarity and searchability\nImproves consistency and quality in projects without a logger utility\n```\n\n```\nfeat(skills): add sync-superpowers skill\n\nPush fork changes and clear Claude cache for skill updates.\n```\n\n```\nfeat(skills): add generating-agents-md skill\n\nSkill for creating/updating AGENTS.md files in repositories with:\n- Standardized template structure\n- Interview questions to capture human-only knowledge\n- Auto-generate vs ask guidance to avoid AI feedback loops\n```\n\n```\nrefactor(skill): split generating-agents-md into separate files\n\n- SKILL.md: core guidance (298 words)\n- template.md: AGENTS.md template structure\n- interview-questions.md: human interview questions per section\n```\n\n```\nfeat(skill): add agent behavior levels (Minimal/Standard/Strict)\n\n- behavior-levels.md: 3 guardrail templates for different codebase needs\n- Updated interview-questions.md with level selection question\n- Updated template.md with Agent Guidelines placeholder\n- SKILL.md stays concise at 316 words\n```\n\n```\ndocs(plan): add backend developer skills implementation plan\n\nCovers 6 priority skills:\n1. database-migrations\n2. api-design\n3. safe-refactoring\n4. error-handling-patterns\n5. dependency-management\n6. performance-profiling\n```",
