        "messages": "## Commit messages\n\n\n```\nprep\n```\n\n```\nupdate\n```\n\n```\ninitial (#1)\n\n* prep\n\n* update\n```\n\n```\nchore: ignore _gitignored/ staging directory\n\nHold-out area for local-only plan files and scratch notes that\nshould not be tracked in the repo.\n```\n\n```\ndocs: establish goodvibes philosophy and divergence log\n\n- Rewrite README with three-principle philosophy and divergence table\n- Create UPSTREAM_DIVERGENCE.md tracking intentional forks\n- Add Goodvibes Execution Preferences section to CLAUDE.md\n```\n\n```\nrefactor: rename framework identity from superpowers to goodvibes\n\nRename the active framework identity throughout the repo:\n- skills/using-superpowers/ → skills/using-goodvibes/\n- docs/superpowers/ → docs/goodvibes/\n- Plugin manifest (.claude-plugin/plugin.json, marketplace.json)\n- package.json name and main path\n- Command namespace: superpowers:* → goodvibes:*\n- Agent namespace: superpowers:* → goodvibes:*\n- Local artifact paths (docs/goodvibes/plans/, ~/.config/goodvibes/, .goodvibes/)\n- Skill cross-references and prose self-references\n- Hooks: session-start injection strings and skill path\n- Scripts: sync-to-codex-plugin.sh publishing identity\n- Tests and docs\n\nPreserved unchanged (intentional):\n- Upstream repo URL (obra/superpowers) in fork notice and comparative refs\n- LICENSE attribution\n- Comparative prose in README (\"Goodvibes is Superpowers retuned for…\")\n- UPSTREAM_DIVERGENCE.md upstream-behavior sections\n- Upstream issue/commit URLs (hook comments, sync script)\n- Legacy-skills migration warning path in hooks/session-start\n  (~/.config/superpowers/skills → tells users migrating off upstream)\n```\n\n```\nfeat(skills): default plan execution to inline, subagent opt-in\n\n- writing-plans: restore user choice; default to inline via executing-plans;\n  updated Execution Handoff and plan header REQUIRED SUB-SKILL line\n- subagent-driven-development: add When to Use This Skill gating section\n- executing-plans: verified as inline-ready (no changes needed)\n\nAddresses the upstream v5 choice removal that forces subagent dispatch\nfor every plan. Opus 4.7 prefers focused one-response execution;\nmandatory subagents fight model instincts.\n```\n\n```\nrefactor(skills): reduce verification-before-completion to gated checklist\n\nOpus 4.7 self-verifies before reporting natively. The full upstream\nceremony duplicates this. Reduce to a gated checklist invoked only for\nspec-compliance cases.\n```\n\n```\nrefactor(skills): tune skill language for Opus 4.7\n\n- No redundant 'think carefully'/'take your time' language found in skills/\n  (upstream already cleaned; nothing removed this pass)\n- Add explicit 'Done Looks Like' sections across 12 preserved skills\n  (Opus 4.7 follows checklists more literally than 4.6)\n- Add 'Scope Boundaries' sections to code-modifying skills:\n  test-driven-development, executing-plans, subagent-driven-development\n```\n\n```\nfeat(skills): add compact-instructions skill\n\nFirst-class support for compact-heavy workflows. Injects project-specific\npreservation guidance before /compact runs.\n\nPreserves:\n- Architectural decisions AND rationale (not just decisions)\n- Rejected alternatives (the first thing compaction typically drops)\n- Exact identifiers\n- Explicitly deferred open threads\n\nAlso surfaces CLAUDE.md promotion candidates.\n\nRegistered in using-goodvibes under Auto-Triggered Skills.\n```\n\n```\nupdates\n```\n\n```\nupdates\n```",
