        "messages": "## Commit messages\n\n\n```\nfeat: implement wave-based parallel execution with triple review\n\nComplete rewrite of superpowers skills for wave-based parallel execution:\n\n**New Architecture:**\n- Wave-based parallel implementation (max 20 subagents per wave)\n- Triple review system (code, security, exception/logging)\n- Dependency tracking (Dependencies + Conflicts per task)\n- Parallel fixer waves (max 20)\n- Zero tolerance for silent failures\n\n**Files Modified (8):**\n1. subagent-driven-development/SKILL.md - Complete rewrite for wave execution\n2. writing-plans/SKILL.md - Add Dependencies, Conflicts, Error Handling\n3. requesting-code-review/SKILL.md - Wave integration\n4. requesting-code-review/code-reviewer.md - Test execution + false positives\n5. brainstorming/SKILL.md - Investigation workflow\n6. subagent-driven-development/implementer-prompt.md - ULTRATHINK + error handling\n7. subagent-driven-development/spec-reviewer-prompt.md - Deprecation notice\n8. subagent-driven-development/code-quality-reviewer-prompt.md - Deprecation notice\n\n**New Files (5):**\n1. subagent-driven-development/fixer-prompt.md - Parallel fixer template\n2. subagent-driven-development/security-reviewer-prompt.md - 11 security categories + gitignore validation\n3. subagent-driven-development/exception-logging-reviewer-prompt.md - Silent failure detection\n4. brainstorming/investigation-prompt.md - Ground-truth discovery\n5. understanding-code/SKILL.md - Investigation-driven code understanding\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n```\n\n```\nfix: clarify NEVER auto-push without user confirmation\n\n- Add explicit \"NEVER push automatically\" to Red Flags (first item)\n- Update Phase 5 to state \"NEVER push automatically. Wait for user to decide.\"\n- Clarify note section: user decides whether to push after completion\n- Remove ambiguous \"Ready to push\" language that could imply auto-push\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n```\n\n```\nfix: remove disable-model-invocation from command\n\nThis was preventing the skill from being invoked via Skill tool.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n```\n\n```\nfix: add disable-model-invocation flag to subagent-driven-development command\n\nThe subagent-driven-development command was missing the 'disable-model-invocation: true'\nflag in its frontmatter, which prevented the skill from loading properly when invoked.\n\nThis flag is required for skill commands to properly display their content to Claude.\n\nChanges:\n- Added disable-model-invocation: true to commands/subagent-driven-development.md\n- Bumped version to 4.1.2-wazyee in plugin.json and marketplace.json\n\nFixes issue where invoking the skill would only return 'Launching skill' message\nwithout showing the actual skill content.\n```",
