        "messages": "## Commit messages\n\n\n```\nFork superpowers for Factory Droid with tool-restricted droids, native worktree, and interactive installer\n\nAdapts obra/superpowers (v5.0.1) for Factory Droid CLI, leveraging\nDroid-specific capabilities not available in Claude Code:\n\nDroids (5 specialized agent definitions):\n- code-reviewer, spec-reviewer, code-quality-reviewer, plan-reviewer:\n  tools: read-only, reasoningEffort: high\n- implementer: full tools, reasoningEffort: medium\n\nHooks:\n- SessionStart: updated for DROID_PLUGIN_ROOT detection\n- SubagentStop: new — auto-reminds review workflow after droid completion\n\nSkills (all 14 updated):\n- Tool names canonicalized (Bash→Execute, Write→Create, WebFetch→FetchUrl)\n- finishing-a-development-branch: enhanced with Create-PR tool\n- using-git-worktrees: enhanced with native droid --worktree\n- using-superpowers: rewritten for Droid skill auto-activation\n\nNew:\n- Interactive Node.js installer (scripts/install.mjs) with macOS one-liner\n- Comprehensive docs at docs/droid/ (architecture, skills, droids, comparison)\n- .factory-plugin/plugin.json (Droid plugin manifest)\n\nRemoved:\n- Claude Code, Cursor, Codex, OpenCode, Gemini platform files\n- Deprecated commands/ directory\n- Platform-specific tests and docs\n```\n\n```\nFix installer: use full Git URL, add safety guards, fix step counter\n\nCritical fixes after local testing:\n- Use full Git URL for marketplace add (shorthand fails)\n- Add isSafeToDelete() guard to prevent deleting source repo or cwd\n- Fix step counter for plugin vs manual install paths\n- Marketplace.json now matches obra/superpowers-marketplace format\n- Add .claude-plugin/marketplace.json for backward compatibility\n```",
