        "messages": "## Commit messages\n\n\n```\nUpdate planning skills to use bd for issue tracking\n\nReplace markdown plan files with bd issues as source of truth:\n\n- writing-plans: Creates bd epic + tasks instead of markdown files\n- executing-plans: Reads from bd, auto-checkpoints on status transitions\n- subagent-driven-development: Same bd integration pattern\n- brainstorming: Creates epic instead of design markdown\n- finishing-a-development-branch: Verifies bd epic closed before merge\n- dispatching-parallel-agents: Optional bd tracking for parallel work\n- requesting-code-review: References bd task instead of markdown path\n\nKey design decisions:\n- Project-local .beads/ directory (not global)\n- Epic → tasks structure (2 levels, 3 when needed)\n- Tasks are commit-able TDD units with dependencies only where blocking\n- Auto-checkpoint notes on status transitions for session resumability\n- TodoWrite for within-task steps, bd for cross-session persistence\n```\n\n```\nAdd bd-issue-tracking skill to superpowers\n\nIncorporates the bd issue tracker skill with:\n- Main SKILL.md with core workflows and commands\n- Reference docs: BOUNDARIES, CLI_REFERENCE, DEPENDENCIES,\n  WORKFLOWS, ISSUE_CREATION, RESUMABILITY, STATIC_DATA\n\nStyle fixes applied:\n- Description starts with \"Use when...\"\n- Placeholder style standardized to [issue-id]\n- Emojis removed from checkpointing section\n- Common Patterns moved to WORKFLOWS.md reference\n\nAdded bd-issue-tracking reference to:\n- writing-plans\n- executing-plans\n- subagent-driven-development\n```\n\n```\nRestructure writing-plans to dispatch subagent for task creation\n\nPlan-writing now happens in a subagent to keep bd CLI calls out of main\ncontext. Skill split into two sections:\n- Dispatching (Main Agent): Template for launching subagent\n- Execution (Subagent): Task creation instructions\n\nEpic creation removed since brainstorming skill now handles that.\nClarified workflow: requires brainstorming first to create epic.\n```\n\n```\nfix(code-reviewer): update model to 'opus' and enhance review guidelines\n```\n\n```\nfix(skills): use bd info for database discovery in worktrees\n\nReplace `ls .beads/` checks with `bd info` which properly discovers\ndatabases in ancestor directories. Prevents accidental creation of\nduplicate .beads directories when running in git worktrees.\n```\n\n```\nfix(settings): remove unnecessary read permissions and clean up allow list\n```\n\n```\nfeat(skills): add writing-claude-md skill for authoring effective CLAUDE.md files\n\nBased on HumanLayer article and baseline testing with subagents. Provides:\n- Three questions filter for content decisions\n- Progressive disclosure pattern (root vs agent_docs)\n- Target length guidelines\n- Review and writing checklists\n- Anti-patterns table\n```\n\n```\nfix(skills): distinguish verification methods for code vs setup tasks\n\nTDD's RGR cycle applies to all tasks, but the verification method should\nmatch the task type. Code tasks use unit tests; setup/infrastructure tasks\nuse command-line verification. Writing test_dependency_installed() that\njust wraps an import is testing the obvious.\n```\n\n```\nfeat(skills): add sprint-review skill for demoing noteworthy completions\n\nWhen something cool lands - unblocks multiple tasks, solves a hard problem,\nor just looks nice - show it off like a dev excited to share their work.\nDon't describe what you did; demo it. Don't force it; only when genuine.\n```",
        "pred": "## What axis\n\n\n**pred_labels:** `integrate-external-system`, `change-artifact-storage`, `add-reference-doc`, `add-sub-workflow`, `swap-execution-model`, `modify-skill-metadata`, `fix-skill-instruction-bug`, `add-decision-rule`, `style-or-format-content`\n\n**families:** `procedure`, `resource`, `lifecycle`, `fix`, `decision`\n\n**what_expression:** `summarize-skill-object-change`, `illustrate-skill-function`, `describe-skill-implementation-principle`\n\n\n## Why axis\n\n\n**why_expression:** `describe-skill-issue`, `describe-skill-objective`\n\n**why_intentions:**\n\n- replace markdown plan files with bd issues as source of truth across planning skills\n\n- add a bd-issue-tracking skill with reference docs\n\n- restructure writing-plans to dispatch a subagent to keep bd calls out of main context\n\n- fix bd database discovery in worktrees to avoid duplicate .beads dirs\n\n- add writing-claude-md and sprint-review skills\n\n- distinguish verification methods for code vs setup tasks\n\n\n## Evidence\n\nUpdate planning skills to use bd for issue tracking, Replace markdown plan files with bd issues; Add bd-issue-tracking skill; Restructure writing-plans to dispatch subagent ... keep bd CLI calls out of main context; use bd info for database discovery in worktrees ... Prevents duplicate .beads; add writing-claude-md skill; add sprint-review skill",
